-- 2012-06-13T15:39:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/russia-stock-movers-gazprom-neft-novatek-magnit-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rose 0.6
percent to 1,346.43 by the close in Moscow, the highest level
since May 12.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Novatek (NVTK RX) rallied 1.1 percent to 326.11 rubles
for a fifth day of gains and the strongest level since May 16.
OAO Gazprom Neft (SIBN RX) added 3 percent to 140.73 rubles.
Russia may increase the natural-gas extraction tax for OAO
Novatek and oil producers at a slower rate than proposed by the
 Finance Ministry  last month, Deputy Prime Minister  Arkady
Dvorkovich  said today.  OAO Magnit (MGNT RX) gained 0.8 percent to 3,576.40 rubles,
the highest since May 10. Russiaâ€™s largest food retailer by
market value rallied after May sales advanced 32 percent from a
year earlier on new store openings.  To contact the reporter on this story:
